Fan Milk Ltd. (FML) , a maker of ice cream
and frozen yogurt in  Ghana , rose the most in almost six months
as profit increased in the first quarter through March.  The shares rose 2.3 percent, to 2.23 cedis as of 1:34 p.m.
in Accra, the capital, the biggest gain since Nov. 2.  Fan Milkâ€™s net income rose 26 percent from a year earlier
to 6.5 million cedis ($3.5 million) in March as revenue advanced
to 35.7 million cedis from 25.5 million cedis, the Accra-based
